<title>USA: Logal cuts jobs, to reduce oper costs.</title>
<headline>Logal cuts jobs, to reduce oper costs.</headline>
<dateline>CAMBRIDGE, Mass. 1996-10-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Logal Educational Software &amp; Systems Ltd said Wednesday it has reduced its workforce by 25 percent and plans to cut its operating costs by about $2.5 million in a reorganization over the next 12 months.</p>
<p>The company said it expects to take a $150,000 charge to its earnings in this year's third quarter as part of the reorganization.  </p>
<p>Logal Chief Executive Yoel Givol said the company will be able to make all of its software products available on the Internet by January 1997, allowing it to immediately scale back its operating expenses.</p>
